useful to take backup and restore in the event of failure.

Ex:
once lose your data if you have snapshot already.
snapshot will give you new volume with existind data.

Snapshot Backup & Restore

• Unmount partition
• Detach volume
• Create new volume from snapshot
• Attach the volume created from snapshot
• Mount it bac


====
create volume 5 G and attach to VM
->fdisk -l

attach and mount it 

from volume --> take snapshot 

once done "detach volume" -> create volume from "snapshot" -> add to VM instance 

